article.description: — Joirdon Karl Nicholas had a season-high 24 points plus 13 rebounds as second-seeded Texas Southern rolled past sixth-seeded Alcorn State 78-55 in the quarterfinals of the Southwestern Athletic Conference Tourney on Thursday.
article.headline: Nicholas lifts Texas Southern over Alcorn State 78-55
article.linkText: Nicholas lifts Texas Southern over Alcorn State 78-55
article.story: BIRMINGHAM, Ala. -- — Joirdon Karl Nicholas had a season-high 24 points plus 13 rebounds as second-seeded Texas Southern rolled past sixth-seeded Alcorn State 78-55 in the quarterfinals of the Southwestern Athletic Conference Tourney on Thursday. John Walker III had 14 points and eight rebounds for Texas Southern (14-8). Michael Weathers added 13 points and eight rebounds. Justin Hopkins had 10 points and nine rebounds. Alcorn State totaled 21 points in the second half, a season low for the team. Tyree Corbett had 23 points and seven rebounds for the Braves (6-13). Byron Joshua added 17 points. Texas Southern plays No. 2 seed Jackson State in the semifinals Friday. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
